ops, Gives Shield\n RELOAD: Place Flesh Beacon\n> Q: SWITCH SPRINT ABILITIES\n> SPRINT 1: Create/Teleport to projection\n> SPRINT 2: Create/Teleport to projection or Teleport to Flesh Beacon or Corrupted Sigil\n> ON HIT BARRICADE: Life Leech Curse"LANGUAGE.controls_bigghoul="> PRIMARY: 攻擊/ 投擲\n> SECONDARY: 抓起 / 釋放\n> RELOAD: 秀肌肉\n> 擊中人類時: Enfeeble\n> 秀肌肉時受到傷害: 吸收傷害轉化爲護甲,提高攻擊傷害"LANGUAGE.controls_crow="> PRIMARY: Peck Sigils / Gibs \n> SECONDARY: Caw / Health Explosion"LANGUAGE.controls_the_lost="> PRIMARY: 開火"LANGUAGE.controls_spectral_revenant="> PRIMARY: Spectral 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 投擲nightmare精華\n> 攻擊擊中人類時: Nightmare and Tremor"LANGUAGE.controls_fetid_maw="> PRIMARY: Poison 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 嘔吐poison\n> RELOAD: 毒球轟炸"LANGUAGE.controls_gonome="> PRIMARY: Burst Claws\n> ON HIT HUMAN: Poison\n> SECONDARY: Gut Throw\n ON GUT THROW HIT: Slow and Prey debuffs\n> RELOAD: Leap"LANGUAGE.controls_harbinger="> PRIMARY: Burst 攻擊\n> 擊中人類時: Poison\n> SECONDARY: 投擲肉球\n 肉球擊中人類時: Slow and Prey debuffs\n> RELOAD: 飛躍"LANGUAGE.controls_breachprowler="> PRIMARY: Attack\n> SECONDARY: Shoot Breach Spikes"LANGUAGE.controls_fleshfire="> PRIMARY: 熾熱一擊\n> SECONDARY: 投擲火球 \nRELOAD: 咆哮"LANGUAGE.controls_dreadmammoth="> PRIMARY: Claw\n> SECONDARY: Leap\n> RELOAD: Moan> ON DEATH: Revive"LANGUAGE.controls_hulk="> PRIMARY: 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 獨輪車泰山壓頂\n> RELOAD: Enrage"LANGUAGE.controls_dread_hulk="> PRIMARY: 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 獨輪車泰山壓頂\n> RELOAD: Enrage"LANGUAGE.controls_cinder_thug="> PRIMARY: Fire 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 衝撞\n> SECONDARY WHILE CHARGING: 躍起,躍起過程中SECONDARY 下落撼地\n> 滿充能衝撞擊中人類: 燃燒爆炸\n> 擊中防線時: 減少prop維修率\n> RELOAD: 上勾拳\n> ON 上勾拳擊中人類: Burning Knockdown Punch"LANGUAGE.controls_cinder_ghoul="> PRIMARY: Fire 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 投擲火球 \n> RELOAD: 嚎叫"LANGUAGE.controls_tarmesh="> PRIMARY: Gunk Claws\n> SECONDARY: Puke Gunk\n> RELOAD: Tar Bomb"LANGUAGE.controls_meteoric_eradicator="> PRIMARY: Fire 攻擊\n> SECONDARY: 投擲火球\n> ON DEATH: Fire Puddle"LANGUAGE.controls_pigeon="> PRIMARY: 拉屎"LANGUAGE.controls_seagull="> PRIMARY: 抓取/放下道具"LANGUAGE.controls_banished_warrior="> PRIMARY: Sword Swing\n> HOLD PRIMARY: Charged Sword Swing\n> SECONDARY: Dash\n> SECONDARY CONNECTION TO HUMAN: Aoe Enfeeble up to to targets\n> RELOAD: Random Buff\n> CHARGE ON BANISHED: Dark Power, Wretched Might, Speed and Shield"LANGUAGE.controls_behemoth=""LANGUAGE.controls_dread_monger=""LANGUAGE.controls_amalgam=""LANGUAGE.controls_moroi=""LANGUAGE.controls_elemental=""LANGUAGE.controls_frostbite=""LANGUAGE.controls_nuclear_terror=""LANGUAGE.controls_poison_anomaly=""LANGUAGE.controls_gonarch=""LANGUAGE.controls_tickledecimator=""LANGUAGE.ZE_WEP_BUY="按下 F3 打開 ZE購買菜單"LANGUAGE.ZE_AFTER_BUY="你購買了一個"LANGUAGE.ZE_WEP_EXIST="你已經擁有此武器"LANGUAGE.ZE_WEP_COOLDOWN="武器菜單正在冷卻(%ss)"LANGUAGE.ZE_NADE_EXIST="你已經擁有一個手雷了!"LANGUAGE.ZE_NADE_COOLDOWN="你的手雷購買正在冷卻 (%ss)"LANGUAGE.ZE_NADE_STOCK="你還剩 %s 個手雷可供購買"LANGUAGE.ZE_WEP_TITLE="按下鍵盤相應的鍵進行選擇"LANGUAGE.ZE_LEADER_TITLE="指揮菜單"LANGUAGE.ZE_ITEM_DROP="Press %s to drop your item."LANGUAGE.ZE_ITEM_DROP_BIND="Bind a key to +zoom to drop your item."LANGUAGE.ZE_ITEM_USE="Press %s (on the green circle) to use your item."LANGUAGE.ZE_ITEM_USE_BIND="Bind a key to +use to use your item."LANGUAGE.help_cat_introduction="Introduction"LANGUAGE.help_cat_survival="Survival"LANGUAGE.help_cat_barricading="Barricading"LANGUAGE.help_cat_upgrades="Upgrades"LANGUAGE.help_cat_being_a_zombie="Being a Zombie"LANGUAGE.help_cont_introduction=[[<p> Welcome to Zombie Survival, the (zombie) survival simulator. ZS allows you to fight zombie attacks, create barricades, and even be part of the undead horde.</p> --"歡迎來到Zombie Survival,這是個(喪屍)生存模擬遊戲. ZS讓你可以攻擊喪屍,建造防線甚至於變成屍潮的一部分."

<p>There are two teams: the survivors and the zombies. The humans win if they survive every wave. Some levels have special objectives to be completed, which may be optional or required to win.
If a human is killed then they'll come back as a zombie, which makes it even more difficult for the remaining humans.</p>  --"總共有兩個陣營：喪屍和人類. 人類的主要目的就是活下來至最後, 而有些地圖則是會有特殊的目標需要完成, 這些目標也許是必須也可能是不必要的. 如果人類被擊殺了, 他們會重生爲喪屍, 這使得活着的人類難度大大提升.

<p>The goal for the zombies is to kill all of the humans, making them all zombies and causing everyone to lose the round.
Alternatively, a zombie can kill four humans to be redeemed. This allows them a second chance at survival and victory.
Remember, the only way to win a round is to be a human when the round ends. Zombies can't technically win the game; zombies can only make everyone else lose!</p> --"喪屍主要的目標是殺死全部人類,把人類全部殺死就算勝利. 可是,喪屍可以通過擊殺指定數量的人類復活. 這讓他們有第二次機會活下來並取得勝利. 溫馨提醒: 只有人類有勝利, 喪屍存在的意義是讓人類輸掉."

<p>A certain amount of people are chosen (or volunteer) for being the starting zombies. This amount is displayed at the bottom of your screen before the round starts.</p> --"在每局遊戲的開場, 會有一定數量的人類被選爲喪屍（自願者）.數量會在遊戲開始前,顯示在屏幕的正下方."

<p><b>Use the buttons up top to get help on more specific things.</b></p>

<p>Tips for this section:
<ul><li>If you leave the game as a human then you'll rejoin as a zombie.</li> --"如果你在還是人類的時候離開遊戲,重新加入你將會轉變爲喪屍"
<li>After a certain amount of time has gone by, even new players will spawn as zombies.</li> -- "經過一段時間後,新加入的玩家將會作爲殭屍出生"
"<li>Use TEAM CHAT when needed. The default key is U and allows you to speak to only your team.</li> -- "必要的時候請使用隊內聊天,默認按U使用隊內聊天"
</ul></p>
]]LANGUAGE.help_cont_survival=[[<p>Tips for this section:
<ul><li>Holding the ZOOM key (default: Z) allows you to move freely through barricades while walking extremely slow.</li> -- "按住“放大”鍵（默認：Z鍵）可以讓你穿越防線,代價是移動的極其緩慢."
<li>If a human is directly killed by a zombie then they will rise again wherever they stand. Make sure you end their misery before they give you any.</li> -- "如果一個人類被殭屍咬死,他們下一次站起來就不再是人類了.請確保在它們對你發起進攻前之前結束他們的痛苦."
<li>You're only given a certain amount of Worth to play with so think carefully what you should get!</li> -- "你的Worth點數是有限的,請仔細考慮你的配裝!"
<li>You can create, save, load, delete, and mark as default carts by pressing F2. This saves a ton of time which could be better spent setting up barricades or creating game plans.</li> -- "你可以按F2鍵來創建、保存、加載、刪除和設置默認配裝.這可以節省大量的時間,而節省下來的時間可以更好地用於建立防線或制定遊戲策略."
<li>A spot that feels safe one moment may be a death trap with more or different types of zombies roaming around. Always allow extra space and a "Plan B" if things get ugly.</li> -- "因爲各種不同類型的殭屍在周圍遊蕩,此刻還算安全的防線可能瞬間就會變成死亡陷阱.如果事情變得不妙,一定要留出額外的空間並準備“B計劃”."
<li>You're useless to your team if you're not doing anything to help. You're even more useless to yourself since you're not getting any points or bigger weapons!</li> -- "如果什麼事情都不做,你就毫無用處.因爲你沒有得到任何分數也就得不到更強大的武器!"
<li>By holding your SPRINT key for about ten seconds while looking at deployed objects that you own, you can pack them up for later use.</li> -- "看着屬於你的放置物並按下“衝刺”鍵約10秒鐘,你可以把它們打包帶走,以便以後使用."
<li>Turrets without owners (a blue light) can be claimed by pressing USE on them. Ownerless turrets will not scan for targets!</li> -- "無主的炮塔（發着藍光的）可以通過按“使用”鍵來認領.無主的炮塔將不會掃描目標!"
<li>Props that aren't nailed to something don't make very good barricades unless they're really heavy.</li> -- "沒有被釘子固定住的物體並不能作爲有效防線使用,除非它們真的很重."
<li>With enough punishment, doors can be thrown off their hinges.</li> -- "對門造成一定的傷害,就可以把它們從鉸鏈上拆下來."
<li>Most props will become red with more and more damage.</li> -- "大多數物體會隨着受到傷害的增加而慢慢變紅."
<li>Zombies can spawn on top of each other if no humans are around to witness it.</li> -- "如果周圍沒有人類,殭屍可以在彼此身上出生."
<li>Most melee weapons have a longer reach than zombie claws. Use this to your advantage if you insist on defending with a melee weapon.</li> -- ""
<li>Players on the same team do not damage or collide with each other and can freely shoot and swing through each other.</li> -- ""
<li>Make sure you use a barricade to your advantage and stay behind it a good distance away from the zombies. Guns have an infinite range, zombie claws do not.</li> -- ""
<li>Your team members aren't always right, don't be a sheep! Zombies like to kill sheep.</li> -- ""
<li>Zombies can see your health, even through walls. Make sure to fall back when hurt as zombies will most likely try to pick you off.</li> -- ""
<li>Don't hide, zombies can sense you through walls and in complete darkness.</li> -- ""
<li>The Horde Meter at the bottom of the screen indicates how much of a damage and knockback resistance you have. Huddle up with other zombies for a big resistance when taking down strongholds!</li> -- ""
<li>If you don't have enough zombies to take down a barricade, try hunting for new "team mates" elsewhere.</li> -- ""
<li>Don't shoot zombies in the green gas! Zombies in the green gas are invincible!</li> -- ""
<li>Zombies are resistant to damage in the chest and even more so in the legs. Make sure you're aiming for the head as some zombies have the ability to get up again if you don't!</li> -- ""
<li>Although zombies take less damage in the legs, shooting them there will slow them down for a short time, enough to allow you or a team member to escape.</li> -- ""
</ul></p>
]]LANGUAGE.help_cont_barricading=[[<p>Barricading is an extremely important part of survival. It may seem like the undead aren't a threat early on but eventually they'll be powerful enough to kill your entire team in a few seconds.</p> -- ""

<p>The only thing keeping the zombies out is a well-built and well-maintained barricade.</p> -- ""

<p>There are a couple of tools that give you the ability to set this up. The one most useful tool is the hammer and nails. This allows you to nail down props which then must have the nails destroyed in order for the zombies to get to you.
Position the prop you want to nail by pressing USE on it to pick it up. You can hold SPRINT while holding it to lock it in place. Then take your hammer and right click where you want the nail to go. It's a good idea to nail the prop to a sturdy object such as a wall instead of other props.
Remember, when a prop is nailed it will forward the damage it takes to the nails themselves. You can repair nails by hitting them with the hammer but eventually they'll become too damaged to repair anymore. You can hold SHIFT with the hammer out to get a view of every single nail deployed on your screen as well as the owner.
If you think a nail is in a bad place or you'd like to reposition a prop, you can remove nails by pointing at it and pressing RELOAD. Be warned, if you take a nail that doesn't belong to you then you will be given a point penalty.</p> -- ""

<p>One other tool is the 'Aegis' Barricade Kit. This quick-deploying tool allows you to place boards on any surface or deploy them between two walls. It doesn't even need props. To use it, you need to position a board in a spot that is legal. The ghost will turn from red to green to let you know.
Deploy a board by pressing PRIMARY ATTACK. Rotate the board by using SECONDARY ATTACK and RELOAD. It uses boards for ammunition so boards you have from the Board Pack work as extra ammunition! You can pack up boards you've deployed by pressing SPRINT while pointing at it.</p> -- ""

<p>Another tool worth noting is the Turret. This tosses bullets at any zombie that gets in the way of its laser. Its only downside is that it requires ammunition. You can refill ammunition by pressing USE on it. This will give you bonus points for helping the team.
To deploy the turret, position it in a way so that the ghost is green. It must be on a solid surface (no props!). Rotate the turret with SECONDARY ATTACK and RELOAD. If you mess up, you can always pack the turret back up by pressing SPRINT while pointing at it. Remember, the turret will only fire at zombies that cross its tracking beam.</p> -- ""

<p>Tips for this section:
<ul>
<li>Use bigger props for barricades. Usually the prop has room for more nails. In addition to that, it even acts as cover from projectiles.</li> -- ""
</ul></p>]]LANGUAGE.help_cont_upgrades=[[<p>Points are obtained through killing zombies, healing team mates, and building defenses.
You can then exchange points in the Points Shop at Arsenal Crates or Sigils.</p> -- ""

<p>Tips for this section:
<ul>
<li>Try planning ahead. Buy extra pistol ammunition in the Worth menu so you have plenty to spare once you get your first upgrade.</li> -- ""
<li>You get points based on how much damage you deal and type of zombie you dealt the damage to.</li> -- ""
<li>Worth and Points are separate. Make sure you spend all of your Worth!</li> -- ""
</ul></p>]]LANGUAGE.help_cont_being_a_zombie=[[<p>Tips for this section:
<ul>
<li>You have an unlimited amount of lives, the humans only have one each. Don't be afraid to attack, attack, attack!</li> -- ""
<li>The regular Zombie class has the ability of durability. The only way to kill you for sure is to get shot in the head or be killed by a melee weapon. You don't need your legs.</li> -- ""
<li>Zombies can spawn on any active nest built.</li> -- ""
<li>With enough practice, you can use props to slam them in to humans from a distance.</li> -- ""
<li>Destroy deployables such as turrets and Arsenal Crates to cripple the humans.</li> -- ""
<li>With enough punishment, doors can be thrown off their hinges.</li> -- ""
<li>Most props will become red with more and more damage.</li> -- ""
<li>The Wraith is completely invisible while standing still or at a distance.</li> -- ""
<li>The Fast Zombie's lunge attack damage scales by how long you're in the air. The more air time you get, the larger the damage. Use your claw attack when in close range!</li> -- ""
<li>In addition to being extremely tough, the Poison Zombie can rip out chunks of its own poison flesh and throw them at humans by pressing SECONDARY ATTACK.</li> -- ""
<li>Most zombie claws have two chances to hit their target. If you "hit" your target when you click your mouse button then you're guaranteed a hit as long as they remain in range.</li> -- ""
<li>The Poison Headcrab's spit projectile can dim vision humans if it hits them in the head.</li> -- ""
<li>Go for the humans with low health! Other zombies are also attracted to them so they should be the easiest targets.</li> -- ""
<li>The Horde Meter at the bottom of the screen indicates how much of a damage and knockback resistance you have. Huddle up with other zombies for a big resistance when taking down strongholds!</li> -- ""
<li>If you don't have enough zombies to take down a barricade, try hunting for new "team mates" elsewhere.</li> -- ""
<li>If an area is too dark, try pressing your FLASHLIGHT button to toggle night vision.</li> -- ""
</ul></p>
]]
